:"2013-12-04t21:26:21z","updated_at":"2013-12-04t21:26:21z","body":"@deepdiver1975 how? why? and how do i change that?"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/29850098","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/6188#issuecomment-29850098","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/6188","id":29850098,"user":{"login":"realrancor","id":2248459,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/f6105e79dfcfb0fcbabb3db061135c08?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f7a70061016eba74d85c060de0f65212d.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"f6105e79dfcfb0fcbabb3db061135c08","url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor","html_url":"https://github.com/realrancor","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-12-04t21:59:04z","updated_at":"2013-12-04t21:59:04z","body":"probably because users can change security specific stuff when they are able to upload a .htaccess file which then gets parsed by your webserver.\r\n\r\nsee also the config.sample.php available here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/owncloud/core/blob/v5.0.13/config/config.sample.php#l35-l36\r\n\r\nfor the blacklisted .htaccess file."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/29851290","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/6188#issuecomment-29851290","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/6188","id":29851290,"user":{"login":"jerrac","id":910764,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/94f514db175a8d425d11b59ddb9914bd?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f2d4e93eae23e52be61d73752b1cd8716.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"94f514db175a8d425d11b59ddb9914bd","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac","html_url":"https://github.com/jerrac","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-12-04t22:14:09z","updated_at":"2013-12-04t22:14:09z","body":"> probably because users can change security specific stuff when they are able to upload a .htaccess file which then gets parsed by your webserver.\r\n\r\nhmm... can't i fix that in the vhost file? only allow .htaccess files to run from the docroot? plus, i keep my data dir outside of owncloud's docroot... guess i get to dive into the apache docs for a bit.\r\n\r\nthanks for pointing out where the blacklist is. :)"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/29851314","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/6188#issuecomment-29851314","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/6188","id":29851314,"user":{"login":"deepdiver1975","id":1005065,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/bdba071ed68da9ce8edae53c364902ef?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f67e101ad9531b7d25697b76e503e062e.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"bdba071ed68da9ce8edae53c364902ef","url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975","html_url":"https://github.com/deepdiver1975","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-12-04t22:14:30z","updated_at":"2013-12-04t22:14:30z","body":">  why?\r\n\r\nthere has been a reason for sure - but i don't remember - sorry\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n> and how do i change that?\r\n\r\nas @realrancor pointed out this can be changed within the config file - but i kindly ask you to be careful - .htaccess is for sure blacklisted for a good reason ...."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/29854198","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/6188#issuecomment-29854198","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/6188","id":29854198,"user":{"login":"jerrac","id":910764,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/94f514db175a8d425d11b59ddb9914bd?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f2d4e93eae23e52be61d73752b1cd8716.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"94f514db175a8d425d11b59ddb9914bd","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac","html_url":"https://github.com/jerrac","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-12-04t22:48:58z","updated_at":"2013-12-04t22:48:58z","body":"so, my solution was to move owncloud's .htaccess directives into the vhost, and disabled .htaccess with ```allowoverride none```.\r\n\r\ni could see .htaccess posing a danger if the data directory was in the docroot, and was not configured with the correct permissions. a user might, then, be able to go to owncloud/datadir/username/files/dir and run an insecure app from there. or something like that. \r\n\r\ndo any of the other core team members remember why they blacklisted .htaccess?\r\n\r\nfor web developers hoping to use owncloud like they do dropbox, blocking .htaccess is very very annoying. i know my coworker keeps all his dev work in dropbox, and there are a lot of .htaccess files in it. if he tried to switch to owncloud, he'd break all his work.\r\n\r\ni consider this something of a bug. see #6189. users expect all their files to sync. when they don't, they get confused. i was able to figure out what was going on, but i'm a web developer and sysadmin. so i know how to do this."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/29855677","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/6188#issuecomment-29855677","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/6188","id":29855677,"user":{"login":"jerrac","id":910764,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/94f514db175a8d425d11b59ddb9914bd?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f2d4e93eae23e52be61d73752b1cd8716.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"94f514db175a8d425d11b59ddb9914bd","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac","html_url":"https://github.com/jerrac","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jerrac/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-12-04t23:08:08z","updated_at":"2013-12-04t23:08:08z","body":"i just posted #6192 so, i'll close this since my initial problem is fixed. "},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/29856057","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/6188#issuecomment-29856057","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/6188","id":29856057,"user":{"login":"vicdeo","id":991300,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/57b8c1e26d502d5414e4b2fb875d2994?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2fe8357fefe8bad5436de368fa5a419461.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"57b8c1e26d502d5414e4b2fb875d2994","url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo","html_url":"https://github.com/vicdeo","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-12-04t23:13:51z","updated_at":"2013-12-04t23:25:05z","body":"@jerrac \r\n>do any of the other core team members remember why they blacklisted .htaccess?\r\n\r\nanyone  with a bit of luck and some knowledge on url construction rules will be able to execute any scripts (not only php, but any that web server is capable to execute) inside the directory that contains prepared .htaccess\r\n\r\nthat's why it was blacklisted. pure security reasons.\r\n\r\nedit: once your data dir is outside of webserver root you don't need to reconfigure apache. \r\nthis is the best security measure by the way :tiger: "},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/29874958","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/6188#issuecomment-29874958","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/6188","id":29874958,"user":{"login":"dragotin","id":1070214,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/af829234b31fb915704c1c65ef48eee0?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f3392afab7f424e10623ba95a941f4d34.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"af829234b31fb915704c1c65ef48eee0","url":"https://api.github.com/users/dragotin","html_url":"https://github.com/dragotin","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dragotin/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dragotin/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dragotin/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dragotin/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dragotin/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dragotin/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dragotin/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dragotin/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dragotin/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-12-05t06:41:18z","updated_at":"2013-12-05t06:41:18z","body":"note that .htaccess is also excluded from sync through the system ignore list."}]